title: Grateful Dead Live at Ventura County Fairgrounds on 1982-07-18
lineage: Cass/1 -> HHb CDR 800 PRO via analog i/o
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues, Loser, Cassidy, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain > Deal

Set 2

Samson And Delilah > Franklin's Tower, Women Are Smarter, Ship Of Fools, Crazy Fingers > Drums > Not Fade Away > Wharf Rat > Sugar Magnolia

E: (I Can't Get No) Satisfaction > Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Sweet! Nice to see one of my masters make it to the Dead Archive collection!
These two Ventura shows where the first ones they played there on the beach & my first West Coast shows. They had camping right there on the beach & it was a pure scene of Love & Grateful Deadness! 

Source was from Sennheiser 441>Sony D5>Marantz 330D
